      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TINEY (2) is a talented gelding who has put together two wins and five minor placings from seven starts this campaign. Produced another fine effort last start when he finished second over 1800m at this track, beaten 2.25 metres. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. Good enough to take out a race like this. CADENCE LANE (5) won at Gawler two runs ago before having her colours lowered at her latest appearance over 2200m at Kapunda, beaten 7 metres. This is a nice drop in grade so she is in the right race to return to form. TRANQUIL BILL (3) won two starts ago then things went wrong last start when he broke and finished a distant eighth over 2070m at Gawler. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. Only needs to get things right to be in the money. JANES GEM (1) is going well, with a minor placing two starts ago then a commendable second last time out over 2230m at this track where she broke in running. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw.",
